article_title: Kim Strassel: Alaska's 'Native Son'—On Thin Ice
article_text:
Wasilla, Alaska

Nick Van Dyke first moved to the Last Frontier as a child, in 1985, and is today as Alaskan as they come. When the 46-year-old isn't running his metal-fabrication shop here, he's out moose hunting, snowmobiling, flying—or entertaining columnists from Washington, D.C.

One thing he's sure about is that Sen. Mark Begich...

twitter.description: In The Wall Street Journal Potomac Watch columnist Kim Strassel writes that Sen. Mark Begich has adopted his party's character-assassination strategy to distract voters from his poor record.
